-- Daimler to Expand Production at Detroit Diesel Plant; Gets Michigan Grant
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-06-18T15:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/daimler-to-expand-production-at-detroit-diesel-plant-gets-michigan-grant.html

          
          
             Daimler AG’s Daimler Trucks North
America will invest about 157 million euros ($194 million) to
“substantially” increase production at Detroit Diesel’s engine
plant in Redford, Michigan, the company said in an e-mailed
statement.  
 The project is receiving a grant of about 46 million euros
from the Michigan Economic Development Corporation, as well as
other state and local tax credits and abatements, according to
the statement.  
